\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid15420377 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Could you give your name and address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I can. Mrs Laura Macaffety, Bryn Golau, Llanfrothen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 When did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 1939.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And you were born in 1904?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 In Rheadr, in Llanfrothen. But I'm not sure if it was Gelli Goch or Rhaedr.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know how many years you lived in Rhaedr?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember moving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well I remember we moved to Gelli Goch to live with my grandfather and grandmother and I remember living there. And we had a very happy time there on the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know why you moved there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well - the reason was that - we were living in half a house and the other family that lived in the same house and more children and so we had to move ojt. But everybody was very kind on those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 After you went to Gelli Goch where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
We went to Tanlan. And we lived there - that was half a house too. You see, we shared. And were there, we had a very interesting, amusing time there too. With the children, there were big crowds of children arou
nd to play with. And you know we used to walk from Gelli Goch to the village to school. When I was about four. It was very interesting in Gelli Goch, you know, we could go riding horses whenever we liked and then we moved to - into the village, in Garreg.
 To Turnpile. And after that we were there. I was there until - I had to go to work. And I used to work even when I was at school 'cos we had to go to work to get a little money. But I mean my}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2689343\charrsid3955477 
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 home life, my mother was very kind and - affectionate but we sti
ll had to go out to work and I had to go and look after some children in Glanwern. There was a crowd of children there and therefore we went along to help, and we'd play with the baby and the little children and we were very happy there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I had two sisters and no brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What order did they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I was in the middle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How many years were there between the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You mean four years each side of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh she must have been in her twenties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well she was the daughter of Gelli Goch, she'd been born and bred athere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she have a job before she married - oh, she didn't marry did she, did she have a job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh she worked as a servant on a farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she still carry on working on the farms after you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she didn't but she was at home, but she used to go out to work from house to ho
use to do washing for people. And my - step-grandmother and grandfather used to look after us while we were living in Gelli Goch and my mother went out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember how many hours a day she'd work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 She'd get up in the morning and get us organi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2689343\charrsid3955477 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
ed and send us out to play or send us off to school and - make our food ready before she left and she'd set out about nine. And then shed be home about - well sometimes late - bout nine. But on other times she might be back a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2689343\charrsid3955477 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 out six. But we always had somebody to look after us all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And usually it was your grandfather and grandmother was it, while you were living with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother do this all her life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, she did. She went out to work like that
 - as far as I can remember. And she'd stay up very late making clothes for us, she was very good at sewing. She'd learnt it all herself. And she always made sure that we had books, Welsh books. But we couldn't afford to have very many books but used to g
e
t - we used to get quite a lot through the chapels. We used to get cymru'r Plant, Tysorf'r Plant and Cymraes and she felt it was very important that we did learn to read. She felt that it was very important for us to have an education in the way that she 
could see it. But we didn't have any further education apart from school. Because I went away to be a servant before I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember how many rooms there were in Gelli Goch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh there weren't many. I should say three. The kitchen and two bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And that was all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, that was all we had. My grandmother and grandfather had the rest. But there was no parlour or anything like that. We were in the smallest part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 That was all the people living in the house, your grandfather and grandmother, your sisters and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. Yes. And also there was a half brother of my mother's living there. And he used to do the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Your mother didn't pay anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she didn't. And she didn't pay any rent either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she do all her washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she take washing in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well not in Gelli Goch she didn't. But when we moved down to Garreg she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said that your mother made and mended all the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, she did. And she made clothes out of old clothes for us, and sometimes she'd stay up on her feet all night before she went to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well yes, sometimes. And then a lady would come to the hou
se to sew and she'd charge two and six a day for being there all through the day. She's called Kit Pritchard, she lives just near here. I don't know if you know her do you? Oh she'd the grandmother of Kenyon and people and she was the one who used to go r
o
und the houses sewing and she'd only charge to and six for making loads of clothes. And then there was a man who came round from Blaenau, he - called a packman, I think that's what they called him, he'd come from Blaenau's shop in Blaenau, and he used to 
sell materials and then she'd make them and then they were quite cheap like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you buy clothes if you bought new ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - and another thing, when we were in Tanlan - when we lived in Tanlan there was a shop there and you could bu
y materials there. Although before that we used to get the things from Blaenau shop in Blaenau. And there were hats there and everything, so therefore we didn't have to go. And it was the father of Mrs Williams the lodge who used to keep this shop in Tanl
an and they'd sell materials and hats, and we'd have new hats from there. And dresses that had been made by }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477 K}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
ate Pritchard. These were made before the Ganamva, the chapel eistedford, but then those had to last for a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you always get new clothes before the Ganamva?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about shoes, did you have new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 hand shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we used to get new shoes before the Ganamva.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 hand shoes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, we did. That's why our feet are all so crooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any tasks to do regularly to help your mother around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, yes, I - I used to love washing and we used to clean, especially my sister did that and then Edith the younger one, well she - you know she used
 to play most of the time. And anyway Edith was much more interested in learning than we were. And - and she'd just be very happy reading if she could have peace to do so. And of course the Sunday school played a very important part, the chapel that is. A
n
d in fact it was very important to people like us in these areas because it taught us to read and to take part in debates, debates about different things. We used to like Sunday school. But not because of - well I mean we did believe that there was a Jesu
s
 Christ and all those sort of things, we'd been taught to believe that, but very soon I came to believe that there wasn't such a thing, must have been when I was about sixteen and I started to rebel against going to chapel. And against lots of things, but
 
I didn't tell very many people. I used to tell my uncle who used to live in Blaenau and he himself was - very - religious, he took a - a leading role in the chapel and I used to have great arguments with him about that there wasn't a - a heaven and that i
t was all quite wrong. I don't know where - I mean I got that idea myself. I just felt that it was impossible for these things to be in being - in existence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember if the older children helped the younger children with things they found diff
icult, did your older sister help you for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes. We had a lot of help like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about your younger sister, did she help you with things, do things for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, but she wasn't so willing really - willing to work as we
 were. But we felt that we were supposed to - we ought to do these things. 'Cos otherwise my mother would have to do all these things herself before she went out. And in fact she tried to do this in order that we wouldn't be different from the other child
ren.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you mother expect you to go to bed at a particular time when you were children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, she did, she liked us to go to bed early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 put you to bed or someone else, your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well my grandmother did when we were in Gelli Goch. And - when we were in Tanlan we used to go on our won because we - sh}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 red a house and there were other children living there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How old were you when you used to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - I'm not very sure. I can't - really
 remember how long we lived in Tanlan, except that I know we left when I was about ten and a half. Yes, I was about ten and a half when we moved to Turnpike.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember if you shared a bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I did. Yes, we all slept in the same bedroom but there were two beds in it. Two in one bed and two in another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Your mother and one sister in one bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And two sisters in the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you have a bath, in front of the fire in a zinc tub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How often did you have to have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we had one every Saturday, and we had to wash every night before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about clean clothes, was that on Saturday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes. Clean clothes happened on Saturday as well. To be ready for Sunday. To respect the Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh in the kitchen. There was a place to cook and everything. And we made all our own bread, well my mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
re there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No. No, there weren't. I mean we never felt that there was anything wrong with what we were doing - eating in the kitchen, we felt it was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What sort of cooking equipment did your mother have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh she had an old fashioned oven which had a fire - you could light a fire underneath it and it had a large grate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - about eight. We used to have bread and milk and I didn't like it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you always have bread and milk for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were all members of the family present at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there any time when you had something different for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You mean you had a different Christmas breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. We had bacon or eggs or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about dinner time and suppertime, when did those happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well my mother would leave dinner for us and the lady next door would heat it up for us. It was usually stew or some sort. But I mean we acc
epted it. We thought it was great. And we used to have - well everyone was kind to us in those days. And say you did a job for someone - someone asked you to pick their potatoes, well then you'd get plenty of potatoes and vegetables from them. Everything 
like that. And you'd get a pitcher of milk for nothing. Life was more - like a - like a family. You felt everyone was related to you. I mean, a lot of us were related but it was more than that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have lunch about midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes - what did we have. Oh we had tinned salmon or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was your mother at home by this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. And we used to have cheese. It was a very important thing in our lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 When did you have supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh - I don't know - about seven, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said your mother baked bread, did she make jam at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, sometimes she did. She'd make plum jam and blackberry jam. It was cheap like that because we used to get them for nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about bottling fruit and vegetables, did she do that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she didn't, no, and our greatest treat then was to have tinned fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she didn't. Very little anyway. Perhaps the odd jar but we didn't really like it. Didn't like anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about making wine or medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh no, no, she didn't do anything like that. Oh but she did make some - medicine. I think there must have been cinnamon in it. If cinnamon was in existence t
hose days. It was cinnamon and honey. Well anyway it was cinnamon to me, I think it was that. I mean, looking back on it that's what it tasted like. And she'd make a big bottle of that - and give it to us when we had colds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 She didn't make beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no, no, not on her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you grow fruit or vegetables at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, because - in those days people would give you a part of a field if you wanted it and you were able to put two rows of potatoes - swedes, carrots, but I'm not sure 
about greens. There may have been cabbage but I don't remember spinach like we have now. And you - you'd get that free, they'd even plant them for you free. So that you had something towards the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother have to buy vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No. No. But - do you know - she had an uncle who lived in Coldty who was related to Evan and he'd bring a whole bag of potatoes, I remember it well, he'd bring them at Christmas time. That was one of our Christmas presents, and he'd bring - homemade f
ruit bread because there was a big brick oven in Coedty and I remember once when I had scarlet fever and I don't think I was getting better and what my aunt did I remember, and my uncle too, they said that I should go there and stay}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  with them and he'd go to the r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
iver and get a little trout for me to eat and of course they had plenty of milk and she'd make rice pudding. I've never tasted such good rice pudding as the rice pudding made in the big oven and she'd put ra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid70738\charrsid3955477 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 sins in with it and they were great big o
nes. And if I didn't eat it all she'd say leave it for me and I'd have it later on. They were very kind in that way. Everybody had something, and specially if you were very poor as we were because you see some people were worse off than others.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember any tinned or dried vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, yes, of course I do. We had pears. I thought the world of the pears and when we visited our aunts there we were absolutely certain of having pears.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, she didn't. She couldn't afford to keep them. My grandmother kept animals and we used to get eggs and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How often in a week would you say you had meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Only tinned salmon. And perhaps corned beef. And in those days everyone killed a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
pig and kept it, so there was plenty of bacon, and they might give you a large piece and you'd have it with roast potatoes. It was lovely. Well I don't know if it was really good, but it was to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever have any extra meat like rabbit through poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no we didn't. No, we didn't poach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember your mother having less food in order that the family should have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, I do. I remember 
her very ill one time. Oh yes. I remember we were in Brondanw - I forgot to tell you that we lived in Brondanw after we went to - after we left Gelli Goch, and I remember her coming home after work and collapsing. She collapsed in a chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to talk during mealtimes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, of course, as much as we liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat out of what had been cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no, no, we had to take what - what was made. We accepted it. I mean we just felt that we were lucky to have any food at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did your mother feel when you left food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, she didn't say anything. For instance we couldn't eat fat, and she didn't mind that. No, she never said anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If 
there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, were you allowed to ask for it or did you have to wait for it to be offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we just took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she expect you to hold your knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. Anyway I think we ate with spoons. She didn't worry about anything like that. Getting it was the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you expected to sit in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to bring toys or books to the table during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No, but it wasn't because she told us that we couldn't and as we got older sometimes we'd have a book at the table, we'd have it in front of us. And sometimes she'd say, haven't you got anything to say
? But she really liked to see us reading. She did like us to read, and she gave us as many books as she could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to leave the table when you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, we never asked to be excused or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the whole family sit down at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have particular places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh - we moved around. I mean if I wanted the sofa I'd get the sofa and somebody else'd want it and they'd get it. We sat anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who prepared the food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there any particular order in which you were served, did she worry about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477 
who}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477  was served first or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, not at all. We had nothing like that, we never had any sort of rules.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know where your younger sister sat before she was able to feed herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Ni, I don't remember. In fact I'm sure she sat on my mother's knee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Fantastically. More than - I mean she was fanta
stically like that and I think that's why, I mean, we didn't think about not having a father. She was sufficient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And could you share your worries with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, everything we used to go home and tell our mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did your mother expect you to behave towards her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Don't really remember. I mean she never demanded anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did she expect you to behave towards your sisters? Did she expect you to behave in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, nothing. Only that - well we were all
owed to quarrel sometimes but on the whole we were fairly easy going and got on well together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If somebody hit you were you allowed to hit that child back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well my mother never used to say anything to us, she just let us go on with it and do wha
t we - we thought we ought to do. But I remember - some English people came to live in the - the Garden House at Plas and we thought the world of these English people. You know the house I mean? The one by the garage. Where John Hughes Weldon was born. An
d
 he lived there. And there were two houses there and I remember thinking the world of these people and there were three of these English girls who'd come there to live and we lived at Brondanw at that time, just up the road, and we'd come home holding the
ir hands and we pretended that we were learning a bit of English. And we used to speak to each other. In fact we didn't speak English, we just made words up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember what sort of person your mother hoped that you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't think so. I mean, I think she hoped that we'd be happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she bring you up to believe that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, only that - belief - believing was important. That's what they had. And she emphasised that we shouldn't
 quarrel and upset other people. I remember that very well. And I was a bit of a rebel. In fact I was much more or a rebel than the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did she think about swearing? Were you allowed to swear at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well she didn't think it was a very good thing, in fact I don't think we did swear. Not much anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If adults were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. If we were there. But as a rule we were out somewhere playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If you did - something that your mother disapproved of what happened? Were you punished at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, we were. If it was something really bad - terrible, then that had to be. We were sent to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 She never hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no. I've no recollection of her ever hitting us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember a particular occasion on which you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, I do. My mother had been given some second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 hand clothes and there was this fur coat. I mean we dressed up in them and we walked up to Croesor with the clothes dragging along the ground and she j
ust happened to be up in Croesor. She was working there. And she saw me and - goodness me I got a row. I remember this red hat, I remember it very well. I'm sure I did look terrible. I used to love dressing up though, but I got a - a terrible row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you feel towards being punished for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I think I just laughed, because I defied everyone. I don't really know if I felt that but anyway it was fun.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about birthdays, were they different of any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes, we use
d to have tea with pancakes, but that was all. And we looked forward very much to having pancakes, all of us had a pancake tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any guests, or a party of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no, no. But we used to have friends in for tea on Sunday because 
on Sunday everybody had time off so we'd have special Sunday teas. All the time, I remember - I remember this boy who used to come to have tea with us, he was a brother to Kinlans father in fact, and he'd come to our house to have tea on Sunday. And I rem
ember once he refused to take a s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 ucer because he said it was too like a plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember anything about Christmas Day? Something you did with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well I remember we had a pretty happy day. There wasn't any - you know, we had be
ef or pork. I remember that, with stuffing and it was lovely. And we'd have a Father Christmas and get some little things, toy tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid70738\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 sets and things, until we became to old, and we'd gets nuts and apples and oranges. And that was all. They couldn't really af
ford to give us things but - they wanted all the children to be the same and round us everybody was the same level, same status.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about musical instruments in your home, did you have any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You know, there weren't any. But I tell you you know 
after I went away to - to be a servant I would have given anything to have been able to play a musical instrument. But I thought that at fifteen I was too old to learn. I mean, if anyone at that time had told me and set me off along that road but I was wo
rking and I felt that I didn't have the right to go and ask for anything but I would have loved to have learnt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, my eldest sister sang and she used to win a lot in the eistedfords. She had a very pretty voice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember singing as a family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes. Yes, on a Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother play games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No, she didn't play games, we played those ourselves. And we'd get some other children in to pla
y with us. We used to have lots of children come in to play with us because there was nothing to get broken.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, all the time. Everything. But Welsh books. But sometimes we'd have a few English magazines from 
somebody, if say, some English people came to the area, and then we'd get those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said you had a few magazines, which were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I can't remember, maybe there was Peg's Paper. Yes, I think we had that. But we used to get Trysorfa'r Plant and 
Cymraes and Cymru'r Plant - we used to get them every week. No, I mean every month. And we'd look forward to them. Then of course we read the Bible. We had to learn that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, we never had newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember seeing your mother reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, I remember her reading the Bible every Sunday. Oh yes, wait a minute, we did get a Welsh newspaper, I think it's gone now, I'm sure it has. I think it was the Rhedegydd - and she'd read those on Sunday, even though 
you weren't supposed to read the newspapers on Sundays, but she used to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, she did, she used to read aloud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember a funeral in the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, I remember my grandfather's funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember what sort of ceremony it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, it was simple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were there a lot of people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. They were quarrymen because my grandfather was a quarryman as well as being a farmer. There was the - all the people f
rom the area, they all came, because by this time they'd gone to - to Balenau to live and everyone from Llanfrothen was there and he was buried in the cemetery of Llamoth, Llamoth chapel in Llanfrothen, because you see, they bought a large piece of land t
o
 - to bury the whole family. But I don't remember the other side, I don't remember my mother's father. Oh wait a minute, yes, it is my mother's father that I remember, but I don't remember my grandmother being - being buried, because she - she died when -
 
before I was born I think 'cos then my grandfather married again. But my mother's mother was the sister of Trevor Thomas's mother, the Post Office. Because she died when she was twenty-seven and she had five children. She'd got married very young and two 
of my mother's sisters died too, they didn't have enough you know, that was the age it was for - and they had to walk down to Portmadoc to get to the doctor and she'd died before the doctor arrived.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said that your father was a quarryman and he was a farmer too at Gelli Goch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, he was. He had a farm but it wasn't enough to keep him and therefore he had to go and work in the quarry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know what he did in the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh he was a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8131310\charrsid3955477 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 man. They were all very good with splitting slates and cutting the rock from the rock face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well they wore black. You had to have those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember going to visit friends, neighbours and relatives, and did you go with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well yes, she'd take us along, but then leave us there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about going out shopping, did your mother take you shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, she did, but when we - we went to get - groceries and things we went by ourselves, we'd go to Penryn which was a great treat
, to go to Penryn. We'd walk to Penrhyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember going on any outings with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No, nothing exceptional. Just going for walks up to Croesor or to Penrhyn and place like that and up to Rhyd, yes, we'd go up there and you know and we'd visit families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever go away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. Only we - only we used to go and see our aunts in Ffestiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you spend your Saturdays in those days?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we used to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we had to stay in the house on Sunday. And we would go to Sunday school in Tanlan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How many times did you go to chapel on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - Selam was too far away so we'd have a sermon in Tanlan and then we'd go to Sunday school. We'd have a sermon either in t
he morning or in the evening and Sunday school in the afternoon, every Sunday. I think we were fairly bad children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. Yes, we wore our best clothes, we kept those aside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to play games on Sunday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, we weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother feel it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. Yes she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. But sometimes she'd just go to the sermon in Tanlan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Which denomination was the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh it was Methodist. The thing was that one half - one part was Methodist and one part was Baptist in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go on the Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no, there weren't any in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember any activities organised by the chapel in which you took part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well we used to have tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8131310\charrsid3955477 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 parties and things and we'd have the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8131310\charrsid3955477 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
s meeting and we used to recite and act plays and we used to be in our element going to the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8131310\charrsid3955477 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 s meeting
. And there was a reading meeting ever Thursday, for about an hour, and we'd learn to read and then we'd be questioned on what we'd read.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you belong to the choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, I did belong to the choir - not that I could sing though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you do, did you compete with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, we used to compete, there used to be -eistedfords, small ones, in the area. And two or three choirs would compete. We did go away once, we went to Portmadoc, it's not far but it was far for us, to a competition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember there being a temperance club connected with the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, I didn't hear of it. There were some though in some areas, there's some in penrhyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, there was a Band of Hope but we - that's what the childrens meeting was, for learning and singing and - reciting and for acting.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there any other club or anything connected with the chapel that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well only the Sayat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What sort of thing was the Sayat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, you used to go to the Sayat, a lot of people went there. Well it was much the same thing as chapel but you had to - yes, you had to learn verses and say them; but you could go and ask the big people questions and they'd go round a
nd - and ask you things like had you accepted the Holy Ghost. And then there was the prayer meeting every Monday night at that time. But all that's finished now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you say grace before meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, never thought of such a thing. Just getting it was the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about saying prayers before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well my mother used to tell us to do that but then it was up to us. But we used to just jump into bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember any sort of family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 We
ll yes, my grandfather, he was a very Godly man and he took part, he was the Leader in the chapel, and he used to say grace before meals, and so we had to when - when we stayed there. But in fact we - you know - we were really quite bad. Naughty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say your grandfather and grandmother were important in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well my grandfather was, but not my grandmother. Not so much, because she was a step-grandmother and she had her own children. And she wasn't because she was a pretty stern woma
n and we hadn't got used to being like that. There was a very hard side to her, she was a very stern woman and we didn't like her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember how many years you lived with your grandfather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh it's difficult to say - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was it very long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No, no, not at all, not at all. It couldn't possibly be because they moved away from there and they went to Blaenau and then we moved and we moved to Brondanw and not to Tanlan straight away. We lived in that small house. But lots o
f people from the school used to come up and visit us there and play with us. Yes, I mean it was quite interesting even though it was amongst enormous poverty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she didn't. Although she was a Liberal. But that's what everybody was as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know why she was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No, I'm afraid I don't know, but I would say it was more - it was quite likely the influence of the hierarchy on her. She felt that they were right, but I don't think she had very much time to think about what was right and what wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember your mother voting in an election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or
 their house if they voted differently from their employer, do you remember anyone coming under this sort of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I know that they did have that sort of influence on people. Power to do that, and that people were forced to do things out of 
fear. But I don't think it was so much the case in this area.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You don't remember a particular occasion when this happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Your mother wasn't a member of a political party was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she ever do any work for any party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 When your mother wasn't working how did she spend her spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh, cleaning and - sewing. She did sew a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, she didn't have time. It was enough to bring us up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 She didn't go out to enjoy herself or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. Only to go and visit someone or go on a trip to Blaenau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 She didn't go to any clubs or pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no. No, no, girls didn't go to those sort of things in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember your mother belonging to a savings club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no, no, she didn't have a ha'penny to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 There were no sort of sick clubs or funeral clubs or boot and sh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8131310\charrsid3955477 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 e clubs or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No. No. But there was a very kind doctor in Penryn and he'd give us medicine if we were ill, he'd come and he'd never ask for anything. He was a very stern doctor though, Doctor Henes he was, and he'd only charge very little, 'cos in those days I mean tha
t's where people were so frightened of going to the doctor in case they got a doctor's bill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you get on with your sisters? Was there one of them you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well we were all pretty friendly with each other and - there 
was no point in anyone doing anything to any of us 'cos we'd all stick together. No, we were pretty friendly and we'd often read a story together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who did you play with as a child, with your sisters or with friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well there
 was a gang of us that used to play together. Because - well everyone was aunties then, and they were you know, you have to - if you look at the figures for North Wales you'll see that more people are related, that the descendants all come from the same f
amily. My grandmother came from over near Maentwrog somewhere and they were the Lloyds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you used to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well when we were in Gargeg and Tanlan we used to play a lot and we used to go up to Pen Gwyllt. Yes, we'd play round about here a
nd there, we'd go over to - Bont Gwernydd where we'd go swimming. I know you won't believe this but a gang of us used to go boys and girls, and of course we hadn't heard of bathing costumes, but we'd just take all our clothes off and go into the water and
 think nothing of it. It was something completely natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go to your friends houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well not much but you know when we were out we used to play hopscotch and chase. We made these things up, you k
now, we had to make our own games up and we used to play snakes and ladders and dominoes as sort of inside games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you free to play with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8131310\charrsid3955477 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 hoever you chose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Your mother didn't encourage you not to play with anyone at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, not at all. It was impossible 'cos there wasn't any feeling of class here. Everyone was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you belong to any youth organisations at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, there was only the Urdd, the Welsh League of Youth and that was in Penrhyn and it was too far to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any particular hobbies in your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, nothing exceptional. I used to like knitting though and reading and sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You didn't have a pet or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No. I would like to - I had this hen which belonged to a farm and I wanted that as a pet, and it used to follow me to school a bit and I called it Mel. It was a sort of - you know, I remember it perfectly well. It had purple feathers, well, 
no, it wasn't purple, sort of pale and I'd call her by her name and I wanted a pet but we didn't have enough space, we couldn't keep one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you collect anything, stamps or cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I used to collect pictures of famous people, I'd 
cut them out of the paper and I'd cut them out and cover them with this thin sort of cellophane paper and - I got a book of them. I remember Lewis Carroll, people like that. People who I thought were great Welsh people, and people like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember doing any gardening as a hobby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't. I don't think I ever did any gardening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go fishing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I didn't. I used to go with people though and I'd tie a string and put a hook on the end and - and put something on 
the end of that and try and fish. But I never caught anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you walk a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, we did. Yes, we used to walk up the cliffs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who did you go walking or fishing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh with boys and girls all together. We made very little distinction between boys and girls then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't think we did much sport except when there was a teaparty or something in school or in chapel. We'd have races and jum
ping and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember hearing of concerts or theatre or music hall when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no I don't, not when I was small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever go to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, I did. I used to go to the flea pit in Port - 
the zinc shed it was and we used to see Charlie Chaplin and different people. It was a great treat. And this is something that used to happen to us once a year in May, we'd go to the Horse and Dog Show in Portmadoc and we'd go on the run. The run - the ra
i
lway between Brontegwyn and Portmadoc, the - where they used to carry slates down - down from Croesor quarry and then - we'd have the run. We'd have to leave school early, before dinner, 'cos we obviously didn't have dinner at school in those days, and we
'd run home all the way in order that we could catch the run at one o'clock and go to Port with it. A horse would pull us along and there'd be wooden planks across for us to sit on. That was a real treat, and I remember the first time I ever had an ice}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8528811\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 cream in Portmadoc.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever have any pocket money at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well we did if we'd worked for it for someone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 But not from your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said nobody came in to help look after the house, did any of your relatives ever come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, they'd come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What soft of things did they do for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well sometimes they'd clean but mainly they made food for us, they looked after us more than anything. That was more important as far as she was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What happened when your mother was ill, did someone come in and help then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. An old aunt came, and she was still alive and she came.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember your younger sister being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 There were a lot of them around were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you see a lot of these relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you meet them, in their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said your mother had many friends, where did she go and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh, you know, round the place. And she eve had some in Penrhyn and they used to come and visit her when they knew she'd be home on a Sunday or something. 'Cos Sunday was the natural day to come visiting or otherwise they'
d come on a nice afternoon sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were they offered things to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. They'd have tea, that was the main thing. And my mother would make pancakes or something like that in a couple of minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did these friends come without invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And neighbours too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. Everybody came without being invited.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You said your mother went visiting friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, she did. And she'd often take us with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 People tell us that in those days people 
made their own amusements, can you remember this, do you remember your mother getting together with friends in order to make amusements?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No sort of musical evenings in the houses or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
A lot of people divide society up into different classes or groups, in the time before 1918 would you say that some people belonged to one group and other people belonged to another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I couldn't say that they did here, I never saw - everyone was together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You don't remember feeling that the landlord or farmers belonged to a different group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I don't remember anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How would you describe the class that you belonged to? What sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well they were the working class. There wasn't a middle class as far as I remember. Wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8528811\charrsid3955477 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477  there was I'm sure, but we didn't notice that there was. But everyone was kind, I mean some had better clothes than others, but nobody looked down on y
ou as somebody low. But the chapels were rather strict with us in that age, I mean, they've altered now but they were quite strict, specially if somebody bad children without being married and people were cut out of the chapel and ignored them a little bi
t
, and that's what they did with my mother. But of course she wasn't the only one, there were a lot of people. And that's why I didn't go to chapel, in fact I stopped going to chapel very early. I refused to go because I felt they were doing wrong things i
n chapel and things like talking about Jesus Christ being friends to everyone. I mean they preached this but didn't practice it and that's why I cut myself off from the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 It was workers that belonged to the same class or group as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember being brought up to treat some people differently from others, to respect people in different ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What do you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you told to respect some people more than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, no. But I'll tell you 
one thing that I did do, I'm sure I wasn't more than four, and - the owner of Croesor quarry and his wife were going in a coach and passing up along the Croesor Road and we were playing in the Bermouth cemetery, me and my two sisters and they came and we 
w
ere supposed to bow or take our hats off or something and I didn't do it and she told my mother and said you know that Annie and Edith and bowed to her, only that I hadn't. You see, it was in me from the beginning. And if I'd been able to sort of develop 
t
his rebellion - I don't know - but I didn't. I couldn't really because my mother was working for them and she would have lost her job so I couldn't think of things like that. But then I was a sort of rebel against them all, and that's what my uncle used t
o say all the time, although he respected a lot of the things I did but - things didn't happen in that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember bowing or curtseying to any other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, the Nysfor people, but then I used to pretend I didn't see them and looked the other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember calling anyone sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No, I don't remember calling anyone that except the teacher. And madam, I never heard that used at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your mother in the form of madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who in the village was considered important? What sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well I'll tell you. May Roberts who lives, you know, down in that big house, you probably know her as Aunty May, she was considered importa
nt and she used to disapprove of people who did things wrong. Because he was a clerk to the council and they lived in a big house, and therefore everyone was slightly afraid of them. But I never was. I never felt that anyone was better than me, although t
hey were in lots of ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you come into contact with these sort of people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. I mean, she was all right. I mean they were like this - sort of so far and no further.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the shopkeepers, do you remember who they mixed with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh with everyone as far as I know. I'm sure they did have their own sort of west though, but I haven't any recollection of me noticing that but - that they made any distinction. The only thing I can remember or any person I can remember is Mrs 
Williams the Lodge's father. And the thing was that my mother wouldn't allow us to go the shop unless we had any money and he always used to say that - that we shouldn't worry and if we were going to go short of food then we should come to the shop }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8528811\charrsid3955477 regard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 less of money. She should at least come and get some food for the children. He was a very nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the ministers and teachers, who did they mix in with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well, they were the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Didn't they mix with the people of the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No. Well yes, they did. They had to mix with some people. If there were some that were a bit better than others, people who went to chapel and things like that. They had to really but then the minister of the chapel - I didn't really go to him for an
ything, come across him much. But they weren't too terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8528811\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
about the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh they were just poor like us. The farmers at that time, they were at their best then, they shared and they gave to anyone that didn't have money. They always did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about employers, the quarry owners of employers on the farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes. I don't really remember many of those except the man who owned the quarry, the one I didn't bow to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well - very poor people and very rich people went to the church if I remember correctly, because I remember the very poor because we went to Harvest Thanks giving and there was one side of the church full of the aristocrats and on the other side ther
e were the others, all polished with red soap, at their best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What would you say was the difference between chapel people and church people? Was there any difference of social standing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - what can I say. Well there was no difference amongst
 the ordinary people, but there was for the hierarchies, the top people, and they used to have - a sort of benevolent attitude, they used to bring charity, but we didn't want charity, we didn't want to be given anything by them. They were O.K. if that did
n't happen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You've already mentioned that amongst the workers there was very little difference in their standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there no distinction amongst the working class at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember any families being described as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well perhaps there were but I can't really remember. I mean, from my point of view I never felt that -people were - were different, except the people who lived -the grand people who lived in the manor houses. Everyone else was just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember any distinction being made between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't. No. Everyone was together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember if your mother felt that she belonged to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well I can't say, I don't think so. Only the same as everybody else. Except that she - she'd been unfortunate really because I mean she'd been brought up like everybody else, herself that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember people moving out of one class into another, moving up the social scale in this area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, I do. I don't deny that there were people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember anyone particularly who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't. But I'm sure people did. I can't say except that they had 
better clothes than we had, than the workers had, but I can't remember anyone being, you know, more respectable - more grand than each other because you see - well we were amongst quarrymen and - their feelings were good enough for everyone, but they felt
 
as one and therefore everyone else - this rubbed off on other people and they made up poetry and - they were very talented people. Especially considering they had so little to eat, and they came back once a week and they worked so hard and sometimes they 
had to get up at four o'clock in order to get up to the quarry in time. They didn't have time to think that they were superior to anyone else. They never felt they were better than their fellow men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you ever remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I do. Sometimes. But very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I was frightened of him of course. 'Cos I always felt I'd done something terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did he treat people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I think they were pretty fie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902122\charrsid3955477 rc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 e in those days. They hadn't come to understand people, they just got hold of them and flung them in jail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, it was a very small rent though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. Not as far as I remember. They never came. I think they were frightened of getting some sort of disease from us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember feeling that your mother had trouble making ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, yes, I do. I remember that well. The thing that we used to dream of as kids was you know, when we started working, the only thing was for us to be servants we couldn't do anything else, we used to dram that we could buy her a fur co
at and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you feel towards this, this struggle that your mother had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh we felt it very badly, we were very sensitive to it. It was really terrible, and she wasn't very strong sometimes and - but she wouldn't take any notice of this and - I'd have to tell her, you know, not to go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did it make any difference to the family if your mother didn't work or was ill and couldn't work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes It did, and she was very upset herself, thinking there was only dying left now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember getting charity from the parish at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she refused to do that, she refused to accept charity. She'd rather go without than do that. 'Co}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5902122\charrsid3955477 s she knew what they were like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 and they were so terribly fierce with people who did
 go to them that she could never face it. They'd come and take something out of your house if you did go. They weren't human, not at all, not - not the men who worked for them. And a lot of it was lack of knowledge but - but you know, she couldn't go - sh
e couldn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If there was someone in your area that people disapproved of very much was there a special way of showing this disapprov}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902122\charrsid3955477 al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 ? In some areas in England they practiced the custom of rough music and making a tremendous noise outside of the ho
use of the person they disapproved of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No, I don't remember that. The thing that people did long ago was get drunk, the men that is, but I've no recollection of what you talk about. No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You don't remember effigies being made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any of your lessons at home or from a private tutor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, not at all. No such thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Four. I think it was four, not three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 When you started what time did you go and what time did you come home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well we must have started pretty early. We used to walk down from Gelli Goch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Starting off about eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Because we were a bit slow and in the winter I got fantastically bad chilblains and it was a terrible job to walk with hard shoes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 When did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh it would be nearly five o'clock by the time we got home. Because we'd stray playing in the ditches and things and gather primroses and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You always went to afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes. Yes, I was there all through the day from the beginning, and
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And it was a primary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And you always walked to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. There and back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And it took about three quarters of an hour to walk down from Gelli Goch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, or a bit more even. Because you know, you know kids, they don't really consider time and they go very slowly and things and get late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go to school with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes I did. And with the people from the next farm, 'cos there were a lot of children there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we had down in the cellar of the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You took your own food with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes we'd take bread - bread and milk. A whole pitcher full.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You carried it down with you did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What other things did you have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh sort of sandwiches and things. We might have some bacon or eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you think of the school, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't. No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the teachers, did you get along with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I liked one but I wasn't fond of the head teacher. Mr Jones, he's dead now, oh he was a terrible man, he used to spit on the ground
 and - oh he was a horrible man. And I didn't see - I thought he wouldn't be teaching and he was very peevish and nasty to everyone. And there were about fifty of us in a class and I remember once two boys beat up the headmaster, they're dead now, they be
a
t him up. But they were really caned for that, they were caned until the dust came out of their clothes. I mean that wouldn't happen now but it did then. And you could see the marks of the canes on them, on their backs. They were called Emlyn and Mel. And
 the thing was that they were - pretty intelligent but he was so peevish he wasn't fit to be a teacher and I was always being sent to the corner because I'd talked, and I'd stand there with my hands on my head for ages. No, I never liked him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember the teachers emphasizing things like manners, tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No, no they never did that. No, they were only concerned with learning - teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they emphasise ways of speaking, did they teach you to speak correct Welshs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No they didn't. And anyway we had English in school. A lot of it was English. We did have a bit of Welsh but mainly it was English.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the girls and boys have the same punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes. I remember having tremendous slaps on my hands with a cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What sort of things were you punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5902122\charrsid3955477 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
l if you were late or if you'd made a blot on your copybook. And then there was when Emlyn and Mel were beaten up and they had such a bad beating. I really worried about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mother take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, she did, she was very keen for us to learn and she would have liked it if we had been able to go ahead, go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she ask you what you'd done at school and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she ever go and see the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh no, no, nobody went. Not in those times. But I remember there was a boy at school, he was a very cruel boy, Elwyn he was called, he was a banker in Llan for some time but I think he's retired now, and he used to
 chase after girls all he time and provoke us and hit us and things like that. And one time he came after this other girl and me and we decided to pay him back, and he was a very thin thing too, even though he could be so cruel and I think half the proble
m
 was that he was the son of the headmaster. We got hold of him and flung him into a patch of stinging nettles. He was so bad he didn't want to get up even and he never dared tell his father because we never had a row about it, I remember him chasing us on
c
e over the - over Pen Gwyllt but my mother was at the door and she came after him and she took him back, every step, to the schoolhouse and she told them that he was chasing after us. And that was the first time that she ever went to the school. And that 
wasn't to the school but to the house, the schoolhouse, and told them that he had to stop him chasing after girls and he wouldn't do anything to boys, this boy, it was always the girls that got it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that the other children in the school came from the same types of home as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well some of them did and some came from better homes because they had a man to earn money, but it made very little difference between us as children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment at all? Did they make favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No - well with us maybe they did with people who were a bit bright and that was - natural enough, because there were so many children in a class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No, we didn't have any of that. The only gangs we had was - because there was a - the Penrhyn gang and they used to gang up on us and we used to go and fight them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were there any children who were left out of everything at school, do you remember seeing anyone on their own all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't, everyone joined in in everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go to another school after Gareg school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I wasn't quite fourteen, I was about thirteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you have stayed on if you'd had the opportunity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes - I would, yes I would have stayed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever do any part time education after that, go to night school or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I didn't. No I didn't, I went to work after that you see. I went away to Cricieth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Have you regretted anything about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes, a lot. A lot. I regret that I didn't go to night school when I was in London. But the trouble is you see I haven't got much confidence. I've got quit
e a lot of fight you know, but I haven't got any confidence, I always think that everybody's better than me. But I - you know, I'm sure that's just insecurity, which there's no point in being that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I don't know, perhaps it did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 While you were at school you've already said that you did some part time work in order to earn a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh it was - it was near home and we were friends with the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh well, we had to take the children for walks, 'cos there was a - there were a crowd of children and we had to wash the dishes and things like that. But I used to run away when I was in the middle of washing the dishes 'cos I didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How many hours did you do this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh well we used to go there after school. And what we'd do would be to have tea there after we came out of school, have tea straight away with the children. And then - wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477  we'd go home about six I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about Saturday and Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well, yes, we'd go on Saturdays but not Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 There weren't any half days or holidays with pay with this job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they pay you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh maybe sixpence a day or a shilling another time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you feel this was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I didn't think. It was just a question of getting a little bit, a little bit of money which was enough. And I lik
ed the people I was working for. They were so nice and so kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you give this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes - every ha'penny I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did she spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well, she'd give some of it back to me. What she'd say in fact, you take 
this and keep it in the box and then you'll be able to buy something that you want. And then I'd do that. Or sometimes I'd give it back to her, she'd take sixpence or a shilling when she was really in need.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And this was for buying food was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes it was. But you know, she never - she never took anything away from us. It was only a loan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that you got on well with the people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, excellently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And your employers treated you O.K.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, 
they were just ordinary people. They were just like us except that they had a farm and a bit of work with the children, 'cos they had babies every minute, but I mean they didn't have very much to give. They might give us say a - a pitcher of milk and a sh
illing and a bag of potatoes or something. And that was a lot really. And sometimes they'd give us butter, you see, that was a lot to us. It was to people in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you feel towards the work? Did you like doing the housework and looking after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh I liked the children, but I was never fond of housework. I also liked working with the animals. I used to like giving them food and things. I think I'd really have enjoyed being on a farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you think doing this part time job changed your attitude to school, did it make you want to leave school earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No it didn't, I never liked school, and therefore it made no difference. To me that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any other part time job before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
not. No, I don't think so, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What was your first full time job and when did you start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I went to Llan Stumdwy to the Post Office in Llan Stumdwy when I was fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was that in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, I'm sure, 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You went there as a servant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, I went to do domestic work. I was so homesick though, just wanted to escape from there. And I wanted to learn things about the Post Office and go into a job in that but they wouldn't let me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh I got it through friends of my mother's, her daughter had been there, and she left because she went home because her mother was ill. They came from Garm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I got up at six and I cleaned around the 
fire, that was to start with, and then I went out and washed the front of the shop, the big - it was a big front, and it was very cold and I was so homesick. And then I had to clean this room because they had a lodger there. I had to clean his room. And h
e
 got up at eight. And then there were two rooms that needed cleaning. And I had to do, like I said, the front of the shop. Then I had to do the washing, everything like that because there was a tailors business at the back and they used to sell the things
 
in the shop as well as it being the Post Office and the tailors would need cups of tea about ten o'clock and I used to have to do that. Then I had to wash, because, you see, he was a - a widower and he had a small baby son. I see the boy now actually, he'
s
 an inspector on the buses. And then there was his brother and his wife and they looked after him and they had one son and I had to do for all of them, I had to clean all their shoes and everything, I wouldn't do that now. And I didn't get a bit to eat un
t
il everyone had got up at eight o'clock. And - and this son, he - he was very clever, the son of the brother and his wife, and his father worked on a farm. But lived with his brother. And you know who he is, he's E.L. Roberts, the scientist in Liverpool, 
and you read about him in the Cymraes sometimes, the Welshman. He was a very clever boy, he went to Portmadoc school, a scholar of ysgro eifonydd.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How many hours did you work a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh there was nothing like that you see, I just worked as long as there was work to be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 done. I just had to do what they said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you work Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And Saturday too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, Saturday too. I would get the odd evening off on a Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you get holidays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, I used to get a holiday every half year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 They didn't pay you for holidays did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How much were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I'm not sure. I think it was about five pounds per six months, but I'm not quite sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you feel that this was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well - do you know - I mean, money was never important to me. All I wanted was to take the money home and then my mother would take me and go shopping if I wanted to buy something. And I'd keep a bit for the next season. But I wasn't happy, I wasn't
 happy at all and I left that place and I went to another place in Llan stumdwy but they kept visitors and I had to work there and I was about fifteen by then. And sometimes I used to have to work until it was midnight there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did you get on with the people you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well it was off and on you know. I felt that they were snobbish. They felt themselves to be better than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you give the money that you got at the end of the seasn to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she wouldn't - she would
n't take it. I used to spend it on - on clothes and; things, but my mother never wanted to take anything from us. But I always wanted to escape home from this place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You've already said you didn't like this type of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did starting to work full time change your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well yes, I'd have loved to have gone back to school. Gone back until I was fifteen anyway. But I used to try and teach myself the so}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 far, the modulator on my own while I was washing the d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 i}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 shes and putting them on the shelf. That's my biggest regret, that I didn't - you know, but there was no encouragement, no encouragement to be had anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And obviously your mother couldn't afford to keep you any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. She couldn't. But I didn
't expect anything from her. I knew it was up to me - myself, nobody else. I couldn't depend on anyone else. But I didn't know where to go and look.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What have you done since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh - I've only done - the - the drudge. The drudgery of work. It's always been the same drudgery but with different people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How many servants were there at the Post Office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh there was only me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You've already explained what you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you sleep and eat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I ate in the kitchen, like they did, but I didn't get it at the same time. And I had a little bedroom, up the stairs.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have the bedroom to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there anywhere in the house where you could go and sit down and be by yourself, apart from the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No. Only my bedroom. Or else I was with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the mistress supervise you very closely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, she just told me what to do and then left me to get on with it. She left me on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You've already explained who the family were and how many there was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, yes, I have. Yes I have, I told you that - that my employer was a widower and he had a son and then there was his brother and there brother's wife and the little boy. My employer's wife died in chil
dbirth. No, sorry, it was his sister and her husband that was there. And they were the housekeepers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 They were housekeepers to him? And then you worked for them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, that's right. I was the slave to them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you feel at ease with the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well yes, I did quite well. I felt all right. But, you know, myself, I didn't really feel fine towards them, I mean I got along with them all right but I mean I didn't feel that I was one of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you call the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I called them Mr and Mrs So and So.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you think they took an interest in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Not none.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your mistress give you any moral guidance at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, none.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever have any free time where you could do what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, I could in the evenings, after the baby had been put to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to go out of the house on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they worry about you and insist that you were in at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh yes they did. I had to be in by about ten. Ten to - no, half past nine to ten. But, you know, unless I'd been to an eistedford or something like that and it had gone a bit later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, terribly. Terribly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What was the trouble, that you didn't have enough companionship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, I didn't have many friends. There was one girl that I got on very well with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there anything that you liked or disliked particularly about the situation you were in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well
 I cannot really say I liked anything about it. I just felt I had to stay there because it was a job. No, I didn't like them, because they had nothing to give to me that would make me happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did the housework go, did you do most of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who did the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about making and mending clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh she did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh she did that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I don't remember, I don't know that I can ever remember anyone spring cleaning. But I wasn't there long you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who looked after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well you see one boy was at school and he sort of looked after himself and I looked after the baby. But she
 didn't really trust me with it, to bath it and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 But you had to feed it and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes I did. And had to look after it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How much did the baby see of its father and aunt and uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well mostly it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 saw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477  its aunt and uncle, the father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 didn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
't seem to take much interest in it. Well I can't remember it anyway. But his aunt doted on him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the baby's bedtime, did you put him to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you play with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did the children see their parents, was there a nursery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, there wasn't a nursery. Not really, because the baby used to sleep in the same bedroom as his aunt and uncle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the schoolboy, did he have any jobs to do about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No, nothing. He only studied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the schoolboy help with the baby at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, nothing. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the schoolboy, did he put himself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well no, no, he went to bed with his mother, his mother put him to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the children share the same bedroom?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No they didn't. The schoolboy slept on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What were the sleeping arrangements for the whole family, how many bedrooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I don't really remember but I suppose that the baby's father slept on his o
wn and then they were in a bedroom with the baby - then there was my bedroom and the schoolboy's bedroom. And also they had a lodger, it was a fairly noble house in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was there a bathroom there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, there wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were the children bathed in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. I'm sure they were. But I never saw anyone having a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know how often they had clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh - every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did the adults eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were the children with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. They were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What sort of fire did they have to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 They had a stove, an old fashioned stove in the kitchen that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the meals, when did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh they had breakfast at eight and then at lunch a
t - at midday. And they had tea at teatime and then they had porridge for supper in the evening - about seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you always have porridge for supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, we always had porridge for supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was everyone present at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, everybody. Only I ate on my own.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you usually have for breakfast and dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well there'd be bacon and eggs for breakfast and fried bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh there'd be meat or something for dinner. It was, you know, it was O.K., there was nothing to complain about but nothing elaborate.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have anything special for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh we'd only have say roast meat on Sunday and have potatoes and veg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about cooking arrangements, did they make their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I think they bought bread. I have no recollection of seeing them making bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about making jam or bottling fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, they didn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 They didn't make pickles or wine? Medicine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they grow fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, there was a pretty good garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they buy any at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember tinned fruit or vegetables there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about dried ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, those too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who did the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well as far as I remember it they had a man to do the gardening and he'd do the outside jobs as well. He sort of tidied them over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How often did they eat meat in a week? Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they eat tinned meat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you all have the same food to eat? Did you have the same food as the family or was it different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I had the same, but sometimes I knew that they were having something better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you eat, did you eat at a different table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I used to eat at the same table as them but after they'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were the children allowed to talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Nobody said anything about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Could they choose what they wanted to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No they couldn't, they had to take what they were given. Take everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they ever leave things uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How was this treated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh - I don't remember anything particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were they allowed to ask for things that were on the table, like the salt, of did they have to wait until it was offered to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh they just took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 So there weren't any sort of formal manners in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No there weren't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the children ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about holding their knives and forks and things like that, did they have to do this in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No they didn't. They just ate at the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Could they leave the table when they wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 The housekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was this done in any particular order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, she just did it as she wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember the children eating at different times to the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I don't remember them not eating with the family except perhaps just before they went to bed, they had something to eat before the
y went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that the child's mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, not easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she show affection to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the children go to her with their worries at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I can't really say because I wasn't there long enough, but I'm sure the schoolboy did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were the fathers easy to talk to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well the boy's father, I liked him. I liked him very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did the parents expect the children to behave towards them? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I can't I'm afraid. I'm sure the children behaved, I don't remember there being any trouble with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did they expect the children to behave to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I don't know, I'm afraid I can't remember. But the children were O.K. with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the parents expect you to tell the children how to behave or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You weren't like a nanny to them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, I wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember how the parents hoped the children would grow up to be like? Presumably they encouraged the clever one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well yes, but I mean there wasn't really any work involved in that because he was naturally clever, and all he did was study, he never went out to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 Did the children s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 ar at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you feel about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If the adults were talking did the children join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, they did if there was something that interested them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember the parents punishing the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
You said a bit about how the parents expected the children to be, what happened if there was a situation in the house where you felt that you were in a sympathy with the children against the parents, did that ever happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well I don't remember anything like that at all. But I think I was probably too young to realize things like that and I didn't take sufficient interest in - in the things that were going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the children's birthdays, was there anything special about those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well it was very straight forward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they have panc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 kes for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh - very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember Christmas Day for this family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I don't think I was there at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, the baby's father used to play the organ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember any of the family singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they sing together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, they did. But not very much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the parents }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4479160\charrsid3955477 play}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477  games at all with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you play games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about books, were there many in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about magazines and newspapers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, everything. Most of them were Welsh, but I'm sure as the boy got older they had some English ones as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember the adults reading at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well the only thing I remember is that the husband of the sister wo
uld come home from work and he'd read. He'd read a lot. He worked on a farm and of course they read the Bible on Sundays. And everyone would read a chapter of that - except for me of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 They didn't disapprove of you not reading the bible did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, they didn't take any notice. And anyway I wouldn't have wondered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember them reading to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. None at all. And I didn't either. I was never given the opportunity to read to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember a funeral in this family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you take the baby out for walks or to go shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, I'd take him out every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you allowed to talk to people when you were out with the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes. I'd meet my friends and talk to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever take the child to your home in Llanfrothen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever go away with your master and mistress for a holiday or an outing, Bank Holiday trip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't. No. I wouldn't have wanted to anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your masters and mistress feel that it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they go to chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How often did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Three times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh no, not - not every - not all o
f them because somebody had to stay behind and look after the baby. And I went to Sunday school. I went to chapel in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh he went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go to the same chapel as your master and mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you sit with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they say grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I don't know, because you see I didn't eat with them so I don't know. But I'm sure they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did your master and mistress take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I never heard them mention it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did either of the men take part in sports, go to races, bet or play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I wouldn't have thought they ever did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 They didn't go to clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Or pubs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the mistress, did she go out on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 I never saw her go out anywhere. I don't think she wanted to spend a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 She didn't have any interests outside the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, not as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the master and mistress go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Only to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What was your master's work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - the - the widower was - worked in the Post Office. And he took the post round too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about his sister's husband, what did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh he worked on a farm. He was a farm servant. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did the master go away from home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And the mistress didn't either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did they have any friends and did the friends call round to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well very few, but they had some brothers and sisters, but I haven't any recollection or much recollection of seeing very many people come there - coming there to have a meal or - or something to drink or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 If friends did come what sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh they were very much the same as them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say the same class as your master and mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes. I would.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that your master and mistress are in a different class or a higher class than ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well he was. He had a brother who I liked very much, he was a very nice man. He wasn't class conscious at all. But I can't remember what he did. I think he probably worked in a bank. He was an exceptional man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Was the mistress in the same class as the master would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Well they were brother and sister so - yes, obviously. But she had married a farm labourer and since her brother was a Postmaster I suppose she thought that he was a bit lower than him. But I mean they were pretty fond of each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that the master and mistress treated some of their friends differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I've no recollection of that. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How did the people who came to see your employers treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 As far as I remember nobody ever said anything to me, I can't remember anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that your masters and mistress were satisfied with their situation in life or would you say that they had aspira
tions of grandeur?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well they were quite satisfied but they wanted their children to get ahead. They were satisfied with what they'd got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Had you met people like your master and mistress before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, yes, I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you feel that they had a different way of life to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5509877\charrsid3955477 irs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477  was a pretty hard life but they had a little more than we did. They had - you know, just a bit more money to be able to do things with. But there was very little difference really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were their manners and ways of behaving different from those of the people you'd mixed with before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, no, they were much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you do after the first world war, you told me you were a domestic servant all your life, when for instance did you go to London?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - wait a minute - oh I don't remember which year it was, but I should think it was about 1924.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How long were you there for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh for about twenty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you have liked to have had a different job in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I would. Oh yes, yes I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What would you have liked to have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I'm not very sure, but maybe I'd have liked to have been a social worker or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You never served an apprenticeship or went through a training period did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you take part in the union's activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Which union did you belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh the Transport and General Workers Union.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would
 you say that employers and workers had the same interest in life, the same way of seeing the world, or would you say they had a different view of the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well I would think different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Why would you say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well - how can I say? To
 me the worker feels that he's working for a man in order to make money for that man, more than for himself. It's as if he had two parts. Nationali}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5509877\charrsid3955477 z}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 ation. I don't know if that's the right word. And then if the employer and worker through nationalisation wo
rk together and not at each other's throats I think it would be different. I mean, to me the worker is like the man at the market. A man with nothing to sell but his labour and I know that's all we've got. But that's what I think, I think there's an enorm
ous difference between the employer and the worker. I mean the employer has the right - has the power to send the worker where he wants and do what he likes with him and put them - put him down. If it wasn't for the unions that is.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that there were distinctions made amongst workers, between craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. Yes there are. An
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 And this is the distinction between craftsmanship and ordinary work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes, that's what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you feel this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Would you say that working changed your attitude to life in any way, how did working affect you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh it did terribly. It taught me to hate everything that - oh how should I say it? It taught me to hate discipline, to hate dictatorship, the dicta
torship of the workers, or the dictatorship over the workers. I feel that they are as good as - as them. And all we get is - you must do this because I tell you to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 After you started working you left home, you - weren't living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did this change your relationship with your mother or your sisters in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
No it didn't, not at all. I felt just the same. Because we used to write to each other and then they knew that you were keeping O.K. We kept in touch through writing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You told me a bit about how you changed your attitude to religion and Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you stop going to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You've already explained why this was haven't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes I have. The only chapel I did go to 
after that was the - the Welsh chapel in London. I went there to get books. And also I kept in contact with the close community round that chapel, the Welsh community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes I did a little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What were your ideas about politics, what were your political ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Oh socialist. Not more than that. I nearly became a communist once, only I think that Socialism is really what I believe in. That's for - you know, what I - as far as I see it, I mean, I think al
l we need is to get the right leadership. We need the right leadership and I think that will change things. But I also believe that we need a lot more young people in politics, because the world's chan}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5509877\charrsid3955477 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 ing and young people see things very differently from 
what we do. But I still think they ought to take a little bit of notice of what older people say, a little counsel from them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you know why you turned out to be a Socialist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well I know that I started to think like that when I was about eighte
en. I started to revolt against ideas which I felt were wrong. 'Cos I'd seen poverty, I'd seen a war between man and man, because all men are the same, all men are equal and maybe some have more education or are more intellectual or whatever that means, b
ut still the - they - they're still men. And if they believe that they're above other men then, even though they call themselves Socialists, they're not, not in my view.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Do you remember ever feeling that you were under pressure from anyone to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, never. I'd only vote for what I believed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were you ever a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. I am a member of the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you work for the Labour party at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about apart from election time, do you still work for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, yes I did. I do whatever I can. But I do everything in fact except public speaking and I'm afraid I can't do that. I'm quite hopeless at that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you change the way in which you
 spent your free time after you left home, apart from taking an interest in politics what else did you do? Were the things that you sort of took up when you were about eighteen things you hadn't been interested in before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Not very much at that time but at - later on I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you go out in the evenings after you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh I used to go with a lot of my friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What did you go and do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well, we used to go to meetings. Anything t
hat was Welsh in fact I'm afraid. We used to go to those because we used to have a feeling of identity with the Welsh aspect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you make new friends at this time, girls or boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Where did you meet these new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you ever bring these friends home to Wales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No. No I didn't. I never really though about it. Somehow it wasn't the thing to do to bring them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes, yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Were there any special places that you went with these particular friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, there were. But we didn't go anywhere sort of - oh we went to meetings, political meetings, wherever there was one we'd go. And we used to go to the theatre. What's the name of that left wing place? You know, in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 You mean the Unity Theatre?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 
Yes, yes, that's right. We used to go there. And we'd do anything link that but sort of interested us. Also we'd go to - to a theatre as well and we'd go to films. When we felt rich we'd do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 While you were in London did you work for the same employer all the time or did you change your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No, I went with - Professor Jordan first. And after that I went to the Williams - Ellis's. Clough Williams Ellis and the 
reason that I stuck with them was that I could go backwards and forwards from - from London to Wales with them because they went backwards and forwards so much and I liked coming home. But I never went with anyone else. I nearly did in fact, only I though
t
 in the end it was better for me to stay where I was. And it's strange, I remember some political meeting in Hapmstead and I remember seeing Annabel Williams Ellis there, Cloughs wife, and I never knew that she was a Socialist too, and she didn't know tha
t I was 'cos she didn't ask her workers what their politics were. And she saw me there. And I didn't know that she was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the friends you made before you went to London, did your parents meet those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh yes, they did, some of them, the ones from this area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 How much did your}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5509877\charrsid3955477  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 mother expect to know where you were when you were working away? Did they insist one letters and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes. I'm sure I did keep sending them letters but I never thought about it much, you know, I just
 used to write down where I was but it wasn't anything particularly major. Because you know, I didn't want to worry them and - if they didn't know where I was they would worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did you have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about the jobs that your sisters did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Well my oldest sister, she did domestic work like I did and she went away to Chester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Did she get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Yes she did. And she's a grandmother now. And then Edith, well she wasn't well most of her life. She got Parkins
on's disease when she was fifteen and she would have been the brilliant one of us, but there you are, it was just unfortunate.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What were your sister's husband's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh he - yes, he had his own business, his own greengrocers business. And - and
 then he went to work in the explosives factory in Penrhyn and - I think he's very good at doing all sorts of electrical things. And he's good at doing - joining. He did - you know, he did the job in the explosives factory first and then he went to - to -
 opened the greengrocer business in Chester.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What about your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11745288 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 Oh well, my husband was unemployed for a long time. And then he got a job with the L.C.C. and he's still with the L.C.C. now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15420377 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10507726\charrsid3955477 What sort of job was that?
